				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="KANPUR: El Desierto Florido" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>KANPUR: El Desierto Florido (&amp;quot;KANPUR: The Flowered Desert&amp;quot;) brings up to four players to the vast and wide Atacama Desert, to keep track of many flower species inside marvelous landscapes of Earth's most arid desert.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players represent nature on the works; they take turns drawing seed tiles, revealing cards that determine where sunlight and water will fall, and then strategically placing and/or moving their tiles depending on the flowers' requirements to bloom. Every flower, even similar species, requires its own conditions to show its colors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Blooming is the main way to obtain Viridian Points or VPs, by registering which species they have seen in their personal album boards. Mission cards work as a boost for players to gain even more VPs; players place their wooden flower markers to track their progress, but once a player fulfills the mission, that player keeps the card and the VPs involved. VPs work like currency as well, as players can pay for Utility Cards to make gardening easier, but be careful: The greater the intervention, the more VPs are paid.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rounds in the game represent seasons in a year, changing weather. In addition, the board has different heights in the middle, making gardening a bit harder than expected, but no worries: Nature is amazing, as this phenomenon is seen every year in the &amp;quot;Norte Grande de Chile&amp;quot; (Great North of Chile).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has 4 game modes: Free for All, 2 vs 2, Cooperative and Solo, as well as 3 difficulty levels: Seed (Easy), Stem (Normal) and Trunk (Hard). Competitive modes add trophy cards that players compete for, as they add VPs at the end of the game. Cooperative and Solo serve as challenges to overcome with strategy and skill.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game comes with a big amount of species to never repeat the same game. Play as you like and take a view on these beautiful flowers!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
